<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2006-02-28c.42.2" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100164" speakername="Lord Davies of Oldham" colon=":" colnum="42"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/pdvn/lds06/text/60228w02.htm#60228w02_spnew2">
	<p pid="c.42.2/1">The number of offences against the person recorded by British Transport Police (BTP) each financial year since 1998&ndash;99 is given in the table below.</p>
	<p pid="c.42.2/2">Information has not been provided for 1997&ndash;98 as there was a change in counting rules in April 1998, introduced by the Home Office, which makes any comparison with data prior to that date not meaningful.</p>
	<table>
		<tbody>
			<tr pid="c.42.2/5"> <td>Offence Category</td> <td>1998&ndash;99</td> <td>1999&ndash;2000</td> <td>2000&ndash;01</td> <td>2001&ndash;02</td> <td>2002&ndash;03</td> <td>2003&ndash;04</td> <td>2004&ndash;05</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="c.42.2/6"> <td>Violence against the person offences</td> <td>5,184</td> <td>5,842</td> <td>5,856</td> <td>5,755</td> <td>7,111</td> <td>8,096</td> <td>9,131</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="c.42.2/7"> <td>Sexual offences</td> <td>1,185</td> <td>1,079</td> <td>1,009</td> <td>1,020</td> <td>1,003</td> <td>1,120</td> <td>1,202</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="c.42.2/8"> <td>Robbery offences</td> <td>2,136</td> <td>2,372</td> <td>2,648</td> <td>3,354</td> <td>2,240</td> <td>2,541</td> <td>2,008</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="c.42.2/9"> <td>Theft of passenger property offences</td> <td>18,346</td> <td>25,323</td> <td>22,741</td> <td>23,710</td> <td>31,151</td> <td>30,190</td> <td>27,655</td> </tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>
	<p pid="c.42.2/12">In reading the figures it should be noted that the Home Office introduced a national crime recording standard (NCRS) that all police forces across England and Wales were required to adopt. BTP adopted this standard on <phrase class="date" code="2002-04-01">1 April 2002</phrase>. The impact of the new recording standard saw an increase in recorded crime nationally.</p>
</reply>
