<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2006-02-28c.44.8" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100802" speakername="Lord McKenzie of Luton" colon=":" colnum="44"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/pdvn/lds06/text/60228w03.htm#60228w03_spnew1">
	<p pid="c.44.8/1">European Council Directive. 69/169/EEC sets a tax and duty free allowance for all travellers bringing goods (excluding wine, spirits, tobacco and perfume) for personal use, including those received as gifts, from outside the EU into the UK.</p>
	<p pid="c.44.8/2">When the directive was first agreed in 1969, the allowance was set at &euro;45 (&pound;36). In 1994 it was increased to &euro;175 (&pound;136), and the UK conversion was revalorised from &pound;136 to &pound;145 in 1995 to reflect exchange rate changes. Since then the allowance has not been revised.</p>
</reply>
